```json
{
  "application": "LSF",
  "details": {
    "queue": "gpua100",
    "gpu": "num=1:mode=exclusive_process",
    "job_name": "AL_Fremstillingsform_8",
    "cores": 4,
    "memory": "12GB",
    "walltime": "24:00",
    "modules": [
      "python3/3.9.14",
      "cudnn/v8.3.0.98-prod-cuda-11.5"
    ],
    "virtual_environment": "./venv",
    "script": "run_BERT_AL.py",
    "arguments": "--target_col \"Fremstillingsform\" --cv 8 --acq_function \"random\""
  }
}
```

This script runs under the LSF (Load Sharing Facility) job scheduler. It defines the job's requirements, including the queue, GPU resources, job name, number of cores, memory per core, walltime limit, and the modules needed.  

The script also defines where output and error files will be stored and sets up the virtual environment for the Python script (`run_BERT_AL.py`) to run.
